{"timestamp":"2026-03-19T10:06:50.374Z","hook_event_name":"PostToolUse","session_id":"0be5f5f9-0c63-4e1a-a140-b68c118374a5","transcript_path":"/home/alexl70/.vscode-server/data/User/workspaceStorage/01bd222c9e9d12cff8e6ef2465541c97/GitHub.copilot-chat/transcripts/0be5f5f9-0c63-4e1a-a140-b68c118374a5.jsonl","tool_name":"runSubagent","tool_input":{"agentName":"Explore","prompt":"Explore the frontend of this link shortener project to understand:\n1. The router setup (src/router/) - what routes exist, how they're configured\n2. The views structure (src/views/) - list all existing views and look at one simple view as a template example\n3. The App.vue structure\n4. The main layout/navigation component - how pages are structured\n5. Any existing static/informational pages\n6. What shadcn/vue components are used (look at components/ folder)\n7. The Caddyfile in deploy/ to understand how the frontend is served\n\nReturn: exact file contents of router/index.ts (or similar), App.vue, and one example view file. Also list all files in src/views/ and src/components/. Also return the Caddyfile content.","description":"Explore frontend structure"},"tool_response":"Perfect! I've mapped out the frontend structure. Here's the complete exploration:\n\n## 1. **Router Setup** ([src/router/index.ts](src/router/index.ts))\n\n```typescript\nimport { createRouter, createWebHistory } from 'vue-router'\nimport type { RouteRecordRaw } from 'vue-router'\nimport { useAuthStore } from '@/stores/auth'\n\nconst routes: RouteRecordRaw[] = [\n  {\n    path: '/',\n    name: 'home',\n    component: () => import('@/views/HomeView.vue'),\n  },\n  {\n    path: '/dashboard',\n    name: 'dashboard',\n    component: () => import('@/views/DashboardView.vue'),\n    meta: { requiresAuth: true },\n  },\n  {\n    path: '/profile',\n    name: 'profile',\n    component: () => import('@/views/ProfileView.vue'),\n    meta: { requiresAuth: true },\n  },\n  {\n    path: '/profile/settings',\n    name: 'profile-settings',\n    component: () => import('@/views/ProfileSettingsView.vue'),\n    meta: { requiresAuth: true },\n  },\n  {\n    // Public route: receives the OAuth redirect from the backend and processes\n    // the hash fragment (#token=…, #pre_registration_token=…, or #error=…).\n    path: '/auth/callback',\n    name: 'auth-callback',\n    component: () => import('@/views/AuthCallbackView.vue'),\n  },\n]\n\nconst router = createRouter({\n  history: createWebHistory(import.meta.env.BASE_URL),\n  routes,\n})\n\nrouter.beforeEach((to) => {\n  const auth = useAuthStore()\n\n  // Protected route — unauthenticated users are sent to the home page.\n  if (to.meta.requiresAuth && !auth.isAuthenticated) {\n    return { name: 'home' }\n  }\n\n  // Home page — authenticated users are sent directly to the dashboard.\n  if (to.name === 'home' && auth.isAuthenticated) {\n    return { name: 'dashboard' }\n  }\n})\n\nexport default router\n```\n\n**Routes Summary:**\n- `/` — Home (public, unauthenticated landing)\n- `/dashboard` — URL management dashboard (authenticated only)\n- `/profile` — User profile page (authenticated only)\n- `/profile/settings` — Profile settings (authenticated only)\n- `/auth/callback` — OAuth callback handler (public)\n\n---\n\n## 2. **Views Structure** — All 8 files in [src/views/](src/views/):\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `HomeView.vue` | Landing page (minimal/simple) |\n| `DashboardView.vue` | Main dashboard with URL list and CRUD |\n| `ProfileView.vue` | User profile display |\n| `ProfileSettingsView.vue` | Profile settings form |\n| `AuthCallbackView.vue` | OAuth callback processor |\n| `DashboardView.spec.ts` | Dashboard tests |\n| `ProfileSettingsView.spec.ts` | Settings tests |\n| `AuthCallbackView.spec.ts` | Callback tests |\n\n---\n\n## 3. **App.vue** — Main Layout & Navigation ([src/App.vue](src/App.vue))\n\n```vue\n<script setup lang=\"ts\">\nimport { RouterView, RouterLink, useRouter, useRoute } from 'vue-router'\nimport { ref } from 'vue'\nimport { useAuthStore } from '@/stores/auth'\nimport { useThemeStore } from '@/stores/theme'\nimport { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'\nimport {\n  Tooltip,\n  TooltipContent,\n  TooltipProvider,\n  TooltipTrigger,\n} from '@/components/ui/tooltip'\nimport { Moon, Sun, Monitor } from 'lucide-vue-next'\nimport { Badge } from '@/components/ui/badge'\nimport {\n  Dialog,\n  DialogContent,\n  DialogHeader,\n  DialogTitle,\n  DialogDescription,\n} from '@/components/ui/dialog'\n\nconst auth = useAuthStore()\nconst themeStore = useThemeStore()\nconst router = useRouter()\nconst route = useRoute()\nconst signInOpen = ref(false)\nconst appVersion = (import.meta.env.APP_VERSION as string | undefined) ?? 'dev'\n\nconst providers = [\n  { id: 'google', label: 'Sign in with Google' },\n  { id: 'microsoft', label: 'Sign in with Microsoft' },\n  { id: 'facebook', label: 'Sign in with Facebook' },\n] as const\n\nfunction signInWith(provider: string) {\n  signInOpen.value = false\n  auth.login(provider)\n}\n\nasync function handleLogout() {\n  await auth.logout()\n  router.push('/')\n}\n</script>\n\n<template>\n  <header\n    class=\"fixed top-0 left-0 right-0 z-50 flex h-14 items-center justify-between border-b bg-background px-6 shadow-sm\">\n    <div class=\"flex items-center gap-6\">\n      <span class=\"text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight\">Link Shortener</span>\n      <Badge variant=\"secondary\" class=\"ml-1 text-xs\">v{{ appVersion }}</Badge>\n      <nav v-if=\"auth.isAuthenticated\" class=\"flex items-center gap-1\">\n        <Button as-child variant=\"ghost\" :class=\"route.name === 'dashboard' ? 'bg-accent' : ''\">\n          <RouterLink to=\"/dashboard\">Dashboard</RouterLink>\n        </Button>\n        <Button as-child variant=\"ghost\" :class=\"route.path.startsWith('/profile') ? 'bg-accent' : ''\">\n          <RouterLink to=\"/profile\">Profile</RouterLink>\n        </Button>\n      </nav>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"flex items-center gap-2\">\n      <TooltipProvider :delay-duration=\"300\">\n        <div class=\"flex items-center\">\n          <Tooltip>\n            <TooltipTrigger as-child>\n              <Button variant=\"ghost\" size=\"icon\" :class=\"themeStore.mode === 'light' ? 'bg-accent' : ''\"\n                aria-label=\"Light mode\" @click=\"themeStore.setMode('light')\">\n                <Sun />\n              </Button>\n            </TooltipTrigger>\n            <TooltipContent>Light mode</TooltipContent>\n          </Tooltip>\n          <Tooltip>\n            <TooltipTrigger as-child>\n              <Button variant=\"ghost\" size=\"icon\" :class=\"themeStore.mode === 'dark' ? 'bg-accent' : ''\"\n                aria-label=\"Dark mode\" @click=\"themeStore.setMode('dark')\">\n                <Moon />\n              </Button>\n            </TooltipTrigger>\n            <TooltipContent>Dark mode</TooltipContent>\n          </Tooltip>\n          <Tooltip>\n            <TooltipTrigger as-child>\n              <Button variant=\"ghost\" size=\"icon\" :class=\"themeStore.mode === 'system' ? 'bg-accent' : ''\"\n                aria-label=\"Follow system settings\" @click=\"themeStore.setMode('system')\">\n                <Monitor />\n              </Button>\n            </TooltipTrigger>\n            <TooltipContent>Follow system settings</TooltipContent>\n          </Tooltip>\n        </div>\n      </TooltipProvider>\n      <Button v-if=\"!auth.isAuthenticated\" variant=\"outline\" @click=\"signInOpen = true\">\n        Sign In\n      </Button>\n      <Button v-else variant=\"outline\" @click=\"handleLogout\">\n        Sign Out\n      </Button>\n    </div>\n  </header>\n\n  <Dialog v-model:open=\"signInOpen\">\n    <DialogContent class=\"max-w-sm\">\n      <DialogHeader>\n        <DialogTitle>Sign In</DialogTitle>\n        <DialogDescription>Choose a provider to sign in to your account.</DialogDescription>\n      </DialogHeader>\n      <div class=\"flex flex-col gap-3 pt-2\">\n        <Button v-for=\"provider in providers\" :key=\"provider.id\" variant=\"outline\" class=\"w-full\"\n          @click=\"signInWith(provider.id)\">\n          {{ provider.label }}\n        </Button>\n      </div>\n    </DialogContent>\n  </Dialog>\n\n  <main class=\"pt-14\">\n    <RouterView />\n  </main>\n</template>\n```\n\n**Structure:**\n- Fixed header with logo, version badge, conditional navigation (auth-only), and theme switcher (Light/Dark/System)\n- Sign-in modal dialog showing 3 OAuth providers (Google, Microsoft, Facebook)\n- Dynamic nav links: Dashboard and Profile (shown only when authenticated)\n- Active route highlighting\n- Main content area with RouterView (pt-14 padding to account for fixed header)\n\n---\n\n## 4. **Example View — HomeView.vue** (Simple/Static)\n\n```vue\n<template>\n  <div class=\"flex min-h-screen flex-col items-center justify-center gap-6 p-8\">\n    <h1 class=\"text-4xl font-bold\">Link Shortener</h1>\n    <p class=\"text-muted-foreground\">Shorten your URLs quickly and easily.</p>\n  </div>\n</template>\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. **Example View — ProfileView.vue** (With State)\n\n```vue\n<script setup lang=\"ts\">\nimport { RouterLink } from 'vue-router'\nimport { useAuthStore } from '@/stores/auth'\nimport { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'\n\nconst auth = useAuthStore()\n</script>\n\n<template>\n    <div class=\"container mx-auto px-6 py-8\">\n        <h1 class=\"text-2xl font-bold mb-6\">Profile</h1>\n        <div class=\"max-w-md space-y-6\">\n            <div class=\"space-y-1\">\n                <p class=\"text-sm text-muted-foreground\">Username</p>\n                <p class=\"text-base font-medium\">{{ auth.user?.username }}</p>\n            </div>\n            <Button as-child variant=\"outline\">\n                <RouterLink to=\"/profile/settings\">Settings</RouterLink>\n            </Button>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</template>\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. **shadcn/vue Components** — All located in [src/components/ui/](src/components/ui/):\n\n- `badge/` — Badge component\n- `button/` — Button component\n- `dialog/` — Modal/dialog component\n- `input/` — Input field component\n- `table/` — Data table component\n- `tooltip/` — Tooltip component\n\nPlus icons from `lucide-vue-next` (Sun, Moon, Monitor, ChevronDown, ChevronUp, Copy, Check, Pencil, Trash2)\n\n---\n\n## 7. **Caddyfile** ([deploy/Caddyfile](deploy/Caddyfile))\n\n```caddy\n# Replace \"yourdomain.com\" with your actual domain name.\n# For production: remove the \"tls internal\" line — Caddy will automatically obtain\n# and renew a TLS certificate via Let's Encrypt. Ports 80 and 443 must be reachable\n# from the internet for the ACME HTTP challenge to succeed.\n# For local/test servers without a public DNS record: keep \"tls internal\" to use\n# Caddy's built-in CA (self-signed). You will need to trust Caddy's root CA on your\n# machine or use curl -k to skip verification.\n\nyourdomain.com {\n    tls internal\n\n    encode zstd gzip\n\n    # Proxy all backend routes to the Go server.\n    handle /auth/* {\n        reverse_proxy localhost:8080\n    }\n\n    handle /user/* {\n        reverse_proxy localhost:8080\n    }\n\n    handle /r/* {\n        reverse_proxy localhost:8080\n    }\n\n    # Serve the Vue SPA for every other path.\n    # try_files ensures deep-links and browser refreshes return index.html.\n    handle {\n        root * /opt/linkshortener/frontend\n        try_files {path} /index.html\n        file_server\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**How it works:**\n- Backend API routes (`/auth/*`, `/user/*`, `/r/*`) → reverse proxy to Go server at `localhost:8080`\n- All other paths → serve Vue SPA from `/opt/linkshortener/frontend` (with SPA routing via try_files)\n- Uses Caddy's internal TLS for local dev; auto-renews Let's Encrypt certs in production\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n✅ **Router:** 5 routes (1 public + 3 authenticated + 1 callback); lazy-loaded components  \n✅ **Views:** 8 files total (4 views + 4 test files); includes home landing, dashboard CRUD, profile display/settings, oauth callback  \n✅ **Navigation:** Fixed header with conditional auth-aware nav, theme switcher, sign-in modal  \n✅ **Components:** 6 shadcn/vue UI components (badge, button, dialog, input, table, tooltip) + lucide icons  \n✅ **SPA Deployment:** Caddy serves Vue SPA with API proxy to backend","tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_018mzHkXm6XQ4a7LpKp6erL5__vscode-1773898184412","cwd":"/home/alexl70/src/pet/linkshortener"}

