localStorage.removeItem('token')` — Token cleared during account deletion |\n| **Line 85** | `if (token.value) { OpenAPI.TOKEN = token.value }` — Token restored to API client after page reload |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Full Auth Callback Flow (Frontend)\n\n**File:** [frontend/src/views/AuthCallbackView.vue](frontend/src/views/AuthCallbackView.vue#L29-L90)\n\nThe callback handler (`onMounted` lifecycle):\n\n| Line | Flow Step |\n|------|-----------|\n| **Line 29** | `function parseHash(): URLSearchParams` — Extracts URL fragment parameters |\n| **Line 48-53** | **Full JWT token received** → calls `auth.handleCallback(token)` → redirects to `/dashboard` |\n| **Line 55-60** | **Pre-registration token received** → opens registration dialog for new users |\n| **Line 62-65** | **Authentication error** → displays error message |\n\n**Key method:** `auth.handleCallback(jwtToken)` at [frontend/src/stores/auth.ts#L42-L50](frontend/src/stores/auth.ts#L42-L50) — Decodes JWT payload, extracts user info (`user_id`, `user_name`, `email`), and populates store.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Backend Auth Routes — Full Content\n\n**File:** [backend/web/routes/auth.go](backend/web/routes/auth.go#L1-280)\n\nThe complete flow:\n\n| Route | Method | Purpose | Lines |\n|-------|--------|---------|-------|\n| **POST /auth/login/{provider}** | GET (bare Gin route) | **Initiates OAuth2 flow** via `gothic.BeginAuthHandler` | 59-108 |\n| **POST /auth/callback** | GET (bare Gin route) | **Completes OAuth2 flow**; issues JWT in redirect fragment `#token=...` | 110-168 |\n| **POST /auth/register** | POST (Huma route) | **New-user registration**; returns JWT in JSON response | 170-191 |\n| **POST /auth/logout** | POST (Huma route) | **Blacklists JWT**; protected by `RequireJWT` middleware | 213-232 |\n| **DELETE /user/account** | DELETE (Huma route) | **Account deletion**; protected by `RequireJWT` middleware | 234-253 |\n\n**Critical redirect detail (Line 155):**\n```go\nc.Redirect(http.StatusFound, redirectTo+\"#token=\"+token)\n```\nThe JWT token is appended as a **URL fragment** (`#token=...`), NOT a query parameter. This is security-critical — fragments are not sent to the server, only visible to JavaScript.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Frontend Router Setup\n\n**File:** [frontend/src/router/index.ts](frontend/src/router/index.ts#L1-57)\n\n| Route | Protected? | Callback Handler | Lines |\n|-------|-----------|------------------|-------|\n| **/** (home) | No, but redirects authenticated users to `/dashboard` | — | 3-6 |\n| **/auth/callback** | Public; receives OAuth redirect | `AuthCallbackView.vue` | 21-27 |\n| **/dashboard** | Yes; requires auth | Guard logic | 8-13 |\n| **/profile** | Yes; requires auth | Guard logic | 15-19 |\n\n**Guard logic (Lines 42-56):**\n- Protected routes (`meta: { requiresAuth: true }`) redirect unauthenticated users to `/`\n- Home page redirects authenticated users to `/dashboard` immediately\n\n---\n\n## 5. Auth API Endpoints\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Purpose | Auth | Response Format |\n|----------|--------|---------|------|-----------------|\n| `GET /auth/login/{provider}` | — | Initiates OAuth2 flow | None | Redirect (bare Gin) |\n| `GET /auth/callback` | — | Completes OAuth2, returns token | None | **URL fragment: `#token=...` or `#pre_registration_token=...`** (bare Gin) |\n| `POST /auth/register` | JSON body | Complete new-user registration | Pre-reg token in body | JSON: `{ \"token\": \"...\" }` (Huma) |\n| `POST /auth/logout` | Bearer JWT | Blacklist token | Required | 204 No Content (Huma) |\n| `DELETE /user/account` | Bearer JWT | Delete account & data | Required | 204 No Content (Huma) |\n\n---\n\n## 6. JWT Usage in API Calls\n\n**OpenAPI Client Configuration:** [frontend/src/lib/api/core/OpenAPI.ts](frontend/src/lib/api/core/OpenAPI.ts#L1-33)\n\n**Token attachment mechanism:** [frontend/src/lib/api/core/request.ts#L130-145](frontend/src/lib/api/core/request.ts#L130-145)\n\nIn `auth.ts` at [line 6 & 30](frontend/src/stores/auth.ts#L6-L30):\n```typescript\nimport { OpenAPI } from '@/lib/api/core/OpenAPI'\n\n// Line 30: After setToken() is called:\nOpenAPI.TOKEN = newToken  // API client automatically adds \"Authorization: Bearer <token>\"\n```\n\nRequest flow:\n1. Token stored → `OpenAPI.TOKEN = newToken`\n2. All subsequent API calls via `DefaultService.*` methods\n3. Request handler in `request.ts` checks if `OpenAPI.TOKEN` is set\n4. If set, adds `Authorization: Bearer ${token}` header automatically\n\n---\n\n## 7. Full Auth Store Content\n\n**File:** [frontend/src/stores/auth.ts](frontend/src/stores/auth.ts) (COMPLETE - 108 lines total)\n\n```typescript\nimport { defineStore } from 'pinia'\nimport { ref, computed } from 'vue'\nimport { OpenAPI } from '@/lib/api/core/OpenAPI'\nimport { DefaultService } from '@/lib/api/services/DefaultService'\n\ninterface User {\n  id: string\n  username: string\n  email: string\n}\n\nconst BACKEND_URL = import.meta.env.APP_BASE_URL as string ?? ''\n\n// Configure the generated API client with the backend base URL.\nOpenAPI.BASE = BACKEND_URL\n\nexport const useAuthStore = defineStore('auth', () => {\n  const token = ref<string | null>(localStorage.getItem('token'))\n  const user = ref<User | null>(null)\n  const deleting = ref(false)\n  const deleteError = ref<string | null>(null)\n\n  const isAuthenticated = computed(() => !!token.value)\n\n  function setToken(newToken: string) {\n    token.value = newToken\n    localStorage.setItem('token', newToken)\n    // Keep the generated API client in sync so authenticated calls include the\n    // Bearer token automatically.\n    OpenAPI.TOKEN = newToken\n  }\n\n  function setUser(newUser: User) {\n    user.value = newUser\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Decode the JWT payload (base64url) and populate the store state.\n   * Called after a successful OAuth callback or registration.\n   */\n  function handleCallback(jwtToken: string) {\n    const parts = jwtToken.split('.')\n    if (parts.length !== 3 || typeof parts[1] === 'undefined') return\n\n    try {\n      const payload = JSON.parse(atob(parts[1].replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/')))\n      setToken(jwtToken)\n      setUser({ id: String(payload.user_id ?? ''), username: payload.user_name ?? '', email: payload.email ?? '' })\n    } catch {\n      // Malformed token — silently ignore; caller should check isAuthenticated.\n    }\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Redirect the browser to the backend OAuth login endpoint, passing the\n   * current origin's /auth/callback as the post-auth redirect target.\n   */\n  function login(provider: string) {\n    const redirectTo = encodeURIComponent(window.location.origin + '/auth/callback')\n    window.location.href = `${BACKEND_URL}/auth/login/${provider}?redirect_to=${redirectTo}`\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Invalidate the JWT on the backend, then clear all local auth state.\n   * Navigation to / is left to the caller (router guards handle it).\n   */\n  async function logout() {\n    if (token.value) {\n      OpenAPI.TOKEN = token.value\n      try {\n        await DefaultService.postAuthLogout()\n      } catch (err) {\n        // Backend rejection (e.g. already-expired token) is non-fatal — we\n        // still clear local state so the user is signed out in the browser.\n        console.warn('logout: backend call failed', err)\n      }\n    }\n    token.value = null\n    user.value = null\n    localStorage.removeItem('token')\n    OpenAPI.TOKEN = undefined\n  }\n\n  // Restore the API client token if we already have one in localStorage.\n  if (token.value) {\n    OpenAPI.TOKEN = token.value\n  }\n\n  /**\n   * Permanently delete the authenticated user's account via the backend API,\n   * then clear all local auth state. Navigation to / is left to the caller.\n   */\n  async function deleteAccount() {\n    deleting.value = true\n    deleteError.value = null\n    try {\n      await DefaultService.deleteAccount()\n      token.value = null\n      user.value = null\n      localStorage.removeItem('token')\n      OpenAPI.TOKEN = undefined\n    } catch (err: unknown) {\n      const message =\n        err instanceof Error ? err.message : 'Failed to delete account. Please try again.'\n      deleteError.value = message\n      console.error('deleteAccount: backend call failed', err)\n    } finally {\n      deleting.value = false\n    }\n  }\n\n  return { token, user, deleting, deleteError, isAuthenticated, setToken, setUser, handleCallback, login, logout, deleteAccount }\n})\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Planning Notes for localStorage → sessionStorage Migration\n\n**Critical dependency points for your migration:**\n\n1. **localStorage calls (4 total):**\n   - Line 17: Initial load\n   - Line 28: Write (in `setToken()`)\n   - Line 78: Clear (in `logout()`)\n   - Line 101: Clear (in `deleteAccount()`)\n\n2. **sessionStorage considerations:**\n   - Cleared automatically when tab closes ✓ (security improvement)\n   - Lost on page reload ✗ (user will need to re-authenticate, but that's acceptable and more secure)\n   - No cross-tab sharing (expected behavior for auth tokens)\n\n3. **Flows affected:**\n   - **Existing users refreshing the page:** Will lose token; must log in again\n   - **OAuth callback:** Works same way (redirect with fragment carries token)\n   - **Login persistence:** Changes from \"remember me\" to \"session-only\" model\n\nPer [ai-instructions/app-auth.md§3.1](ai-instructions/app-auth.md#31-auth-store-srcstoresauths), the auth store is the single source of truth for token persistence — no component should access storage directly. Your migration stays within the store boundary, so compliance is maintained.","tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_0144WB6b4kdTzD7DgLesdSA9__vscode-1773898184527","cwd":"/home/alexl70/src/pet/linkshortener"}

