re-reg token (line 178), creates user, issues full JWT\n   - Frontend receives JWT, stores it via `auth.handleCallback()`\n\n### **JWT/Token Handling:**\n\n- **Full Session JWT** ([jwt.go](backend/web/routes/jwt.go#L18-L21)): user_id, user_name, email + standard claims, 24-hour expiry\n- **Pre-Reg Token** ([jwt.go](backend/web/routes/jwt.go#L23-L26)): Provider, ProviderUserID, Email, DisplayName, 10-minute expiry\n- **Token sent in requests**: Bearer token in `Authorization` header (lines 78–79 request.ts)\n- **API Client config** ([OpenAPI.ts](frontend/src/lib/api/core/OpenAPI.ts#L13)): `WITH_CREDENTIALS: false`, `TOKEN` resolver\n\n### **CORS & Middleware:**\n\n- **CORSMiddleware** ([cors.go](backend/web/routes/cors.go)): \n  - Dev: echoes any origin\n  - Prod: validates against `APP_BASE_URL`\n  - Handles OPTIONS preflight (204 No Content)\n- **RequireJWT**: Protects `/auth/logout` and `/user/account` endpoints; claims injected into context","tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01HSfNZputwihmkPkaxHHBgo__vscode-1773898184547","cwd":"/home/alexl70/src/pet/linkshortener"}

