{"timestamp":"2026-03-19T11:57:48.110Z","hook_event_name":"PreToolUse","session_id":"65209c52-bf87-4bac-93c2-d9a6cba43c0f","transcript_path":"/home/alexl70/.vscode-server/data/User/workspaceStorage/01bd222c9e9d12cff8e6ef2465541c97/GitHub.copilot-chat/transcripts/65209c52-bf87-4bac-93c2-d9a6cba43c0f.jsonl","tool_name":"memory","tool_input":{"command":"create","path":"/memories/session/plan.md","file_text":"# Plan: HttpOnly Cookie-Based JWT Auth (Issue #2)\n\n## TL;DR\nReplace JWT-in-localStorage with `HttpOnly SameSite=Strict` cookie-based auth. Backend sets the cookie after OAuth and registration; frontend removes all token storage and calls `GET /auth/me` to restore user info on load. Both JWT middleware functions read from the cookie instead of `Authorization: Bearer`.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1 — Backend\n\n### 1.1 New helper: session cookie factory\n- Add `setSessionCookie(w http.ResponseWriter, token string, isDev bool)` and `clearSessionCookie(w http.ResponseWriter, isDev bool)` helpers in `backend/web/routes/auth.go` (or a new small file `backend/web/routes/cookie.go`).\n- Cookie spec: name=`linkshortener_session`, HttpOnly=true, SameSite=Strict, Secure=(not dev), Path=\"/\", MaxAge=86400.\n\n### 1.2 Update both JWT middlewares to read cookie\n- `RequireJWT` (used by protected Huma group in auth.go) — `backend/web/routes/middleware.go` lines 92–118.\n- `RequireJWTGlobal` (used in main.go) — `backend/web/routes/middleware.go` lines 26–60.\n- Replace `c.GetHeader(\"Authorization\")` / `strings.TrimPrefix(…, \"Bearer \")` with `c.Cookie(\"linkshortener_session\")`.\n- Remove the `\"Bearer \"` prefix logic entirely.\n\n### 1.3 Update OAuth callback — set cookie, drop fragment token\n- `backend/web/routes/auth.go` line ~150: replace\n  `c.Redirect(http.StatusFound, redirectTo+\"#token=\"+token)`\n  with `setSessionCookie(c.Writer, token, isDev)` + `c.Redirect(…, redirectTo)`.\n- isDev flag: pass it from `RegisterAuthRoutes` (add parameter or read env inside helper).\n\n### 1.4 Update `/auth/register` — set cookie, return user info\n- Replace `AuthTokenResponse` (returns `{ token }`) with new `AuthUserResponse` (returns `{ user_id, user_name, provider_email }`).\n- Set the session cookie via the Huma response header field (`SetCookie string `header:\"Set-Cookie\"``).\n- New cookie value built by the `setSessionCookieHeader` helper that returns a formatted Set-Cookie string.\n- Update response mapper in `backend/web/mappers/auth.go`.\n- Update `backend/web/viewmodels/auth.go`: add `AuthUserBody`, `AuthUserResponse`, keep `AuthTokenBody`/`AuthTokenResponse` only if referenced elsewhere (they can be removed).\n\n### 1.5 Update `/auth/logout` — clear cookie\n- The logout Huma handler must clear the cookie via header field in the output struct.\n- Change the output type from `*struct{}` to a new struct with `SetCookie string `header:\"Set-Cookie\"`` carrying the clear-cookie directive.\n- Keep existing blacklist logic unchanged.\n\n### 1.6 Add `GET /auth/me` Huma endpoint\n- Register on `protectedAPI` (cookie-gated group).\n- Reads `GetJWTClaimsFromContext(ctx)`, returns `{ user_id, user_name, provider_email }`.\n- New viewmodels: `MeBody`, `MeResponse` in `backend/web/viewmodels/auth.go`.\n\n### 1.7 Update CORS middleware\n- `backend/web/routes/cors.go`: add `c.Header(\"Access-Control-Allow-Credentials\", \"true\")` alongside the existing Allow-Origin header (only when origin is allowed).\n- No wildcard origin is already guaranteed — cookie + credentials requires specific origin, which the existing code already does.\n\n### 1.8 OpenAPI security scheme (informational)\n- In `backend/main.go`, add a cookie security scheme to `humaConfig` before calling `humagin.New`:\n  ```go\n  humaConfig.Components.SecuritySchemes = map[string]*huma.SecurityScheme{\n      \"session\": {Type: \"apiKey\", In: \"cookie\", Name: \"linkshortener_session\"},\n  }\n  ```\n- Update all `Security: []map[string][]string{{\"bearer\": {}}}` references in auth.go and urls.go to `{\"session\": {}}`.\n\n### 1.9 Backend tests to update\n- `backend/web/routes/auth_test.go`: \n  - `TestRegister_ValidPreRegToken_ReturnsJWT` → assert Set-Cookie header is present instead of `resp[\"token\"]`.\n  - `TestLogout_ValidToken_Returns204` → assert Set-Cookie clear-cookie header.\n  - Middleware tests: send `Cookie: linkshortener_session=<token>` instead of `Authorization: Bearer <token>`.\n- `backend/web/routes/middleware.go` tests if they exist.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2 — Frontend\n\n### 2.1 Enable credentials in generated API client\n- `frontend/src/lib/api/core/OpenAPI.ts`: change `WITH_CREDENTIALS: false` → `WITH_CREDENTIALS: true`.\n- Do NOT edit `request.ts` (generated file); `WITH_CREDENTIALS: true` already enables `credentials: config.CREDENTIALS` which is already `'include'`.\n\n### 2.2 Regenerate OpenAPI client\n- Run `npm run generate` (or equivalent) after backend changes to update `DefaultService` with the new `/auth/me` endpoint and changed register response type.\n\n### 2.3 Rewrite auth store (`frontend/src/stores/auth.ts`)\nKey changes:\n- Remove `token` ref and all localStorage usage.\n- `isAuthenticated` — computed from `user !== null`.\n- Add `fetchMe()` action: calls `DefaultService.getAuthMe()`, populates `user` on success, clears user on 401.\n- Change `handleCallback()`: no longer parses JWT, instead calls `fetchMe()`.\n- Change registration success path in `AuthCallbackView.vue`: call `auth.fetchMe()` instead of `auth.handleCallback(result.token)`.\n- Remove `OpenAPI.TOKEN = …` everywhere (cookie is sent automatically).\n- Remove `setToken()` helper (no longer needed).\n- `logout()`: call backend logout (no Bearer header needed; cookie sent automatically), then clear `user` ref.\n- `deleteAccount()`: call backend delete, then clear `user` ref.\n- Restore auth state on startup via `fetchMe()` called in `main.ts`.\n\n### 2.4 App startup auth init (`frontend/src/main.ts`)\n- After `app.use(pinia)`, call `await useAuthStore().fetchMe()` before `app.mount('#app')`.\n- This ensures router guards have correct auth state from the first navigation.\n\n### 2.5 Update `AuthCallbackView.vue`\n- `submitRegistration()`: remove `if ('token' in result) { auth.handleCallback(result.token) }` check; instead call `await auth.fetchMe()` then `router.replace('/dashboard')`.\n- `onMounted`: the `#token` branch, replace `auth.handleCallback(token)` with `await auth.fetchMe()` (cookie already set by backend redirect).\n  - Actually, the fragment `#token=…` no longer exists after the change — the backend will redirect without the fragment. The `onMounted` logic can be simplified: no `params.get('token')` branch. Just check for `pre_registration_token` or call `fetchMe()`.\n  - New simplified flow: if pre-reg token in hash → show registration dialog; else → call `fetchMe()` → if user found → `/dashboard`; else show error.\n\n### 2.6 Frontend tests to update\n- `frontend/src/stores/auth.spec.ts`: remove localStorage assertions, add fetchMe mock, remove token-related tests.\n- `frontend/src/views/AuthCallbackView.spec.ts`: update to not rely on token parsing.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3 — Update instruction file\n\n### 3.1 `ai-instructions/app-auth.md`\n- Section 3.1 Auth Store: remove \"The JWT token may be persisted to localStorage only through the auth store's actions.\" Replace with documentation of cookie-based approach.\n- Section 2.3 JWT Tokens: add note that JWT is delivered as an HttpOnly cookie (not in response body or URL fragment for session JWTs).\n- Section 4 Security Checklist: add cookie spec (HttpOnly, SameSite=Strict, Secure in prod).\n\n---\n\n## Relevant files\n\n- `backend/web/routes/middleware.go` — both RequireJWT and RequireJWTGlobal; replace Bearer header reading with cookie reading\n- `backend/web/routes/auth.go` — callback sets cookie; register sets cookie header; logout clears cookie; add /auth/me\n- `backend/web/routes/auth_test.go` — update tests for cookie-based auth\n- `backend/web/viewmodels/auth.go` — add AuthUserBody/AuthUserResponse/MeBody/MeResponse; remove AuthTokenBody/AuthTokenResponse\n- `backend/web/mappers/auth.go` — update/replace UserToAuthTokenResponse with UserToAuthUserResponse\n- `backend/web/routes/cors.go` — add Allow-Credentials header\n- `backend/main.go` — add session cookie security scheme to humaConfig\n- `frontend/src/lib/api/core/OpenAPI.ts` — set WITH_CREDENTIALS: true\n- `frontend/src/stores/auth.ts` — remove localStorage/token, add fetchMe()\n- `frontend/src/main.ts` — call fetchMe() before mount\n- `frontend/src/views/AuthCallbackView.vue` — update callback and registration success paths\n- `frontend/src/stores/auth.spec.ts` — update tests\n- `frontend/src/views/AuthCallbackView.spec.ts` — update tests\n- `ai-instructions/app-auth.md` — update security documentation\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n1. `go test ./...` — all backend tests pass\n2. `npm run test` — all frontend tests pass\n3. TypeScript compile: `npx tsc --noEmit` (no errors)\n4. Manual: log in via Google OAuth → verify cookie `linkshortener_session` is set as HttpOnly in DevTools → no token in localStorage\n5. Manual: refresh page → verify still authenticated (cookie persists; fetchMe() succeeds)\n6. Manual: open new tab to `/dashboard` → verify still authenticated (cookie shared across tabs)\n7. Manual: logout → verify cookie is cleared and user is redirected to `/`\n8. Manual: new user flow → registration dialog appears → after registration, user is redirected to `/dashboard`\n\n---\n\n## Decisions\n\n- Pre-registration token stays in URL fragment — it's a 10-minute, one-time-use, non-session credential; moving it is out of scope for this fix and only weakly improves security\n- `SameSite=Strict` chosen over `Lax` — provides CSRF protection without needing a separate CSRF token mechanism\n- No separate CSRF token added — `SameSite=Strict` is sufficient for modern browsers\n- `fetchMe()` called before app mount in `main.ts` — avoids race condition with router guards\n- `/auth/logout` still blacklists the JTI — belt-and-suspenders; even though the client clears the cookie, the token should be invalidated server-side (addresses issue #6 partially)\n- Bearer auth security scheme removed from OpenAPI spec — replaced with cookie-based `apiKey` scheme\n"},"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01Kds2geWgzBgW274ZbhPP9B__vscode-1773898184570","cwd":"/home/alexl70/src/pet/linkshortener"}

