does.\n    46\t\n    47\t### 1.8 OpenAPI security scheme (informational)\n    48\t- In `backend/main.go`, add a cookie security scheme to `humaConfig` before calling `humagin.New`:\n    49\t  ```go\n    50\t  humaConfig.Components.SecuritySchemes = map[string]*huma.SecurityScheme{\n    51\t      \"session\": {Type: \"apiKey\", In: \"cookie\", Name: \"linkshortener_session\"},\n    52\t  }\n    53\t  ```\n    54\t- Update all `Security: []map[string][]string{{\"bearer\": {}}}` references in auth.go and urls.go to `{\"session\": {}}`.\n    55\t\n    56\t### 1.9 Backend tests to update\n    57\t- `backend/web/routes/auth_test.go`: \n    58\t  - `TestRegister_ValidPreRegToken_ReturnsJWT` → assert Set-Cookie header is present instead of `resp[\"token\"]`.\n    59\t  - `TestLogout_ValidToken_Returns204` → assert Set-Cookie clear-cookie header.\n    60\t  - Middleware tests: send `Cookie: linkshortener_session=<token>` instead of `Authorization: Bearer <token>`.\n    61\t- `backend/web/routes/middleware.go` tests if they exist.\n    62\t\n    63\t---\n    64\t\n    65\t## Phase 2 — Frontend\n    66\t\n    67\t### 2.1 Enable credentials in generated API client\n    68\t- `frontend/src/lib/api/core/OpenAPI.ts`: change `WITH_CREDENTIALS: false` → `WITH_CREDENTIALS: true`.\n    69\t- Do NOT edit `request.ts` (generated file); `WITH_CREDENTIALS: true` already enables `credentials: config.CREDENTIALS` which is already `'include'`.\n    70\t\n    71\t### 2.2 Regenerate OpenAPI client\n    72\t- Run `npm run generate` (or equivalent) after backend changes to update `DefaultService` with the new `/auth/me` endpoint and changed register response type.\n    73\t\n    74\t### 2.3 Rewrite auth store (`frontend/src/stores/auth.ts`)\n    75\tKey changes:\n    76\t- Remove `token` ref and all localStorage usage.\n    77\t- `isAuthenticated` — computed from `user !== null`.\n    78\t- Add `fetchMe()` action: calls `DefaultService.getAuthMe()`, populates `user` on success, clears user on 40