  100\t\n   101\t---\n   102\t\n   103\t## Phase 3 — Update instruction file\n   104\t\n   105\t### 3.1 `ai-instructions/app-auth.md`\n   106\t- Section 3.1 Auth Store: remove \"The JWT token may be persisted to localStorage only through the auth store's actions.\" Replace with documentation of cookie-based approach.\n   107\t- Section 2.3 JWT Tokens: add note that JWT is delivered as an HttpOnly cookie (not in response body or URL fragment for session JWTs).\n   108\t- Section 4 Security Checklist: add cookie spec (HttpOnly, SameSite=Strict, Secure in prod).\n   109\t\n   110\t---\n   111\t\n   112\t## Relevant files\n   113\t\n   114\t- `backend/web/routes/middleware.go` — both RequireJWT and RequireJWTGlobal; replace Bearer header reading with cookie reading\n   115\t- `backend/web/routes/auth.go` — callback sets cookie; register sets cookie header; logout clears cookie; add /auth/me\n   116\t- `backend/web/routes/auth_test.go` — update tests for cookie-based auth\n   117\t- `backend/web/viewmodels/auth.go` — add AuthUserBody/AuthUserResponse/MeBody/MeResponse; remove AuthTokenBody/AuthTokenResponse\n   118\t- `backend/web/mappers/auth.go` — update/replace UserToAuthTokenResponse with UserToAuthUserResponse\n   119\t- `backend/web/routes/cors.go` — add Allow-Credentials header\n   120\t- `backend/main.go` — add session cookie security scheme to humaConfig\n   121\t- `frontend/src/lib/api/core/OpenAPI.ts` — set WITH_CREDENTIALS: true\n   122\t- `frontend/src/stores/auth.ts` — remove localStorage/token, add fetchMe()\n   123\t- `frontend/src/main.ts` — call fetchMe() before mount\n   124\t- `frontend/src/views/AuthCallbackView.vue` — update callback and registration success paths\n   125\t- `frontend/src/stores/auth.spec.ts` — update tests\n   126\t- `frontend/src/views/AuthCallbackView.spec.ts` — update tests\n   127\t- `ai-instructions/app-auth.md` — update security documentation\n   128\t\n   129\t---\n   130\t\n   131\t## Verification\n   132\t\n   133\t1. `go test ./...` — all backend tests pass\n   134\t2. `npm run test` — all frontend tests pass\n   135\t3. TypeScript compile: `npx tsc --noEmit` (no errors)\n   136\t4. Manual: log in via Google OAuth → verify cookie `linkshortener_session` is set as HttpOnly in DevTools → no token in localStorage\n   137\t5. Manual: refresh page → verify still authenticated (cookie persists; fetchMe() succeeds)\n   138\t6. Manual: open new tab to `/dashboard` → verify still authenticated (cookie shared across tabs)\n   139\t7. Manual: logout → verify cookie is cleared and user is redirected to `/`\n   140\t8. Manual: new user flow → registration dialog appears → after registration, user is redirected to `/dashboard`\n   141\t\n   142\t---\n   143\t\n   144\t## Decisions\n   145\t\n   146\t- Pre-registration token stays in URL fragment — it's a 10-minute, one-time-use, non-session credential; moving it is out of scope for this fix and only weakly improves security\n   147\t- `SameSite=Strict` chosen over `Lax` — provides CSRF protection without needing a separate CSRF token mechanism\n   148\t- No separate CSRF token added — `SameSite=Strict` is sufficient for modern browsers\n   149\t- `fetchMe()` called before app mount in `main.ts` — avoids race condition with router guards\n   150\t- `/auth/logout` still blacklists the JTI — belt-and-suspenders; even though the client clears the cookie, the token should be invalidated server-side (addresses issue #6 partially)\n   151\t- Bearer auth security scheme removed from OpenAPI spec — replaced with cookie-based `apiKey` scheme\n   152\t","tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01PZjbhsCiQqJW5QHXHBCMxG__vscode-1773898184571","cwd":"/home/alexl70/src/pet/linkshortener"}

