{"timestamp":"2026-03-19T13:20:22.322Z","hook_event_name":"PreToolUse","session_id":"eb843e64-0a7c-4651-9d8b-a61baa911ffb","transcript_path":"/home/alexl70/.vscode-server/data/User/workspaceStorage/01bd222c9e9d12cff8e6ef2465541c97/GitHub.copilot-chat/transcripts/eb843e64-0a7c-4651-9d8b-a61baa911ffb.jsonl","tool_name":"memory","tool_input":{"command":"create","path":"/memories/session/plan.md","file_text":"# Plan: Per-IP Rate Limiting (Security Issue #3)\n\nTL;DR: Add three tiered per-IP rate limiters (auth/API/redirect) controlled by env vars, wire trusted-proxy config so Gin sees real client IPs behind Caddy, and add `golang.org/x/time/rate` as a new approved direct dependency.\n\n---\n\n## Decisions\n- **golang.org/x/time/rate**: Approved as new direct dependency.\n- **Burst sizes**: Fixed per tier — not configurable. Auth=1, API=10, Redirect=30.\n- **Trusted proxies**: Configured in the same PR via new `TRUSTED_PROXIES` env var.\n\n## New env vars (all optional with documented defaults)\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `RATE_LIMIT_AUTH_RPM` | `5` | Max req/min per IP for auth endpoints (`/auth/login`, `/auth/register`) |\n| `RATE_LIMIT_API_RPM` | `60` | Max req/min per IP for authenticated API (`/user/`) |\n| `RATE_LIMIT_REDIRECT_RPM` | `120` | Max req/min per IP for public redirects (`/r/`) |\n| `TRUSTED_PROXIES` | `127.0.0.1` | Comma-separated list of trusted reverse proxy IPs for correct ClientIP extraction |\n\nBurst sizes (fixed, not env-configured): auth=1, API=10, redirect=30.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1 — Config (no dependencies between steps; can be done in parallel)\n\n**Step 1** — `backend/config/env.go`:\n- Add `RATE_LIMIT_AUTH_RPM`, `RATE_LIMIT_API_RPM`, `RATE_LIMIT_REDIRECT_RPM` to `optionalDefaults` with string defaults `\"5\"`, `\"60\"`, `\"120\"`.\n- Add all three to `numericOptional` so Validate() enforces integer parsing.\n- Add `TRUSTED_PROXIES` to `optionalDefaults` with default `\"127.0.0.1\"` only (NOT numericOptional — it's a string).\n\n**Step 2** — `ai-instructions/app-environment.md`:\n- Add all 4 vars to the §4.2 table.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2 — Dependency\n\n**Step 3** — Add `golang.org/x/time` to `go.mod`:\n- Run `go get golang.org/x/time` inside `backend/`.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3 — Rate Limiter Middleware\n\n**Step 4** — Create `backend/web/routes/ratelimit.go`:\n\nInternal types:\n- `ipLimiterEntry` struct: `limiter *rate.Limiter`, `lastSeen time.Time`\n- `perIPStore` struct: mutex, `map[string]*ipLimiterEntry`, `rpm int`, `burst int`\n  - `newPerIPStore(rpm, burst int) *perIPStore` — creates map, starts background cleanup goroutine (ticker every 1 min, deletes entries last seen > 2 min ago)\n  - `Allow(ip string) bool` — get-or-create limiter for IP, update lastSeen, call `limiter.Allow()`\n  - Uses `rate.NewLimiter(rate.Every(time.Minute/time.Duration(rpm)), burst)` per IP\n\nPublic interface:\n- `type RateLimitTier struct { PathPrefixes []string; Store *perIPStore }`\n- `NewRateLimitTier(pathPrefixes []string, rpm, burst int) RateLimitTier` — convenience constructor\n- `RateLimitMiddleware(tiers []RateLimitTier) gin.HandlerFunc`:\n  - For each request, iterate tiers, check `strings.HasPrefix(path, prefix)` for each prefix in tier\n  - On match: call `tier.Store.Allow(c.ClientIP())` — if false, `c.AbortWithStatusJSON(429, gin.H{\"error\": \"too many requests\"})`\n  - No matching tier: pass through\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4 — Wire up in main.go\n\n**Step 5** — `backend/main.go`:\n- After `router := gin.New()` (currently `gin.Default()` — but that's issue #9; keep as-is for now):\n  - Parse `TRUSTED_PROXIES` env var: `strings.Split(..., \",\")` with space trimming\n  - Call `router.SetTrustedProxies(trustedProxies)` — exit on error\n- Create three `RateLimitTier`s using `NewRateLimitTier`:\n  - Auth tier: prefixes `[\"/auth/login\", \"/auth/register\"]`, rpm from `RATE_LIMIT_AUTH_RPM`, burst=1\n  - API tier: prefix `[\"/user/\"]`, rpm from `RATE_LIMIT_API_RPM`, burst=10\n  - Redirect tier: prefix `[\"/r/\"]`, rpm from `RATE_LIMIT_REDIRECT_RPM`, burst=30\n- Add `router.Use(routes.RateLimitMiddleware(tiers))` before CORS and JWT middleware.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 5 — Tests\n\n**Step 6** — Create `backend/web/routes/ratelimit_test.go` (package `routes_test`):\n- Test: requests within limit are allowed (200)\n- Test: requests exceeding RPM return 429 (use rpm=1, burst=1, fire 2 requests)\n- Test: different IPs have independent buckets (each gets its own limit)\n- Test: paths not matching any tier pass through (no rate limit applied)\n- Test: matching only happens on the correct prefix (e.g., `/auth/me` does NOT match `/auth/login` or `/auth/register` prefixes)\n- Use the same pattern as `middleware_test.go` — `gin.New()` + `httptest.NewRecorder()`\n\n---\n\n## Relevant files\n- `backend/config/env.go` — add 4 vars to optionalDefaults; 3 to numericOptional\n- `ai-instructions/app-environment.md` — §4.2 table\n- `backend/web/routes/ratelimit.go` — new file\n- `backend/web/routes/ratelimit_test.go` — new file\n- `backend/main.go` — trusted proxies + rate limit middleware wiring\n- `backend/go.mod` + `go.sum` — new dependency\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n1. `go build ./...` from `backend/` passes after changes.\n2. `go test ./web/routes/...` — all rate limit tests pass.\n3. `go test ./config/...` — validation tests still pass (new vars get defaults).\n4. `go vet ./...` passes.\n5. Manual: spin up dev server, hit `POST /auth/register` 6 times in rapid succession from the same IP — expect HTTP 429 on the 6th hit.\n\n---\n\n## Scope boundaries\n- Included: rate limiting, trusted proxy config, env var documentation, tests.\n- Excluded: replacing `gin.Default()` with `gin.New()` (that's issue #9), any change to existing auth/redirect/url route logic.\n"},"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_012X3FEH1TX3bKAqScgWQY5K__vscode-1773898184718","cwd":"/home/alexl70/src/pet/linkshortener"}

