T Calls:\n1. [auth.go:155](backend/web/routes/auth.go#L155) – `/auth/callback`: \"Existing user — issue full JWT\"\n2. [auth.go:205](backend/web/routes/auth.go#L205) – `POST /auth/register`: After user registration\n3. [auth_test.go:17](backend/web/routes/auth_test.go#L17) – Test: `TestRegister_ValidPreRegToken_SetsSessionCookie`\n4. [jwt_test.go:17](backend/web/routes/jwt_test.go#L17) – Test: `TestCreateJWT_RoundTrip`\n5. [jwt_test.go:25](backend/web/routes/jwt_test.go#L25) – Test: `TestCreateJWT_JTIPresent`\n6. [jwt_test.go:35-37](backend/web/routes/jwt_test.go#L35-L37) – Test: `TestCreateJWT_TwoTokensHaveDifferentJTI` (two calls)\n\n### CreatePreRegToken Calls:\n1. [auth.go:169](backend/web/routes/auth.go#L169) – `/auth/callback`: \"New user — issue pre-registration token\"\n2. [jwt_test.go:87](backend/web/routes/jwt_test.go#L87) – Test: `TestCreateAndParsePreRegToken_RoundTrip`\n3. [jwt_test.go:111](backend/web/routes/jwt_test.go#L111) – Test: `TestCreatePreRegToken_ValidRoundTrip`\n\n### ParseJWT Calls:\n1. [middleware.go:41](backend/web/routes/middleware.go#L41) – `RequireJWTGlobal`: Validates cookie token\n2. [middleware.go:99](backend/web/routes/middleware.go#L99) – `RequireJWT`: Validates cookie token in protected group\n3. [jwt_test.go:28, 40, 41, 50, 60, 74, 206](backend/web/routes/jwt_test.go#L28) – Various JWT tests\n\n### ParsePreRegToken Calls:\n1. [auth.go:195](backend/web/routes/auth.go#L195) – `POST /auth/register`: Validates pre-reg token in request body\n2. [jwt_test.go:91, 100, 119, 135](backend/web/routes/jwt_test.go#L91) – Various pre-reg token tests\n\n---\n\n## 3. JWTClaims Usage Sites\n\n**Type Definition** [jwt.go:19-24](backend/web/routes/jwt.go#L19-L24):\n```go\ntype JWTClaims struct {\n    UserID   int64  `json:\"user_id\"`\n    UserName string `json:\"user_name\"`\n    Email    string `json:\"email\"`\n    jwt.RegisteredClaims\n}\n```\n\n**Field Access:**\n- `claims.UserID` – [auth.go:239](backend/web/routes/auth.go#L239), [auth.go:280](backend/web/routes/auth.go#L280) (GET /auth/me, DELETE /user/account)\n- `claims.UserName` – [auth.go:261](backend/web/routes/auth.go#L261) (GET /auth/me)\n- `claims.Email` – [auth.go:261](backend/web/routes/auth.go#L261) (GET /auth/me output shows `ProviderEmail`)\n- `claims.ID` (jti field) – [auth.go:251](backend/web/routes/auth.go#L251) (blacklist.Add), [middleware.go:52](backend/web/routes/middleware.go#L52)\n- `claims.ExpiresAt.Time` – [auth.go:251](backend/web/routes/auth.go#L251) (Pass to blacklist.Add)\n- `claims.Subject` (sub) – [jwt_test.go:54](backend/web/routes/jwt_test.go#L54) (test assertion)\n\n**Retrieval from Context** (10+ locations):\n- [urls.go:24, 49, 71, 94](backend/web/routes/urls.go#L24) – URL operations\n- [auth.go:239, 261, 280](backend/web/routes/auth.go#L239) – Auth handlers\n- Using `GetJWTClaimsFromContext(ctx)` - [middleware.go:68](backend/web/routes/middleware.go#L68)\n\n---\n\n## 4. Token Validation Middleware\n\n**Location:** [middleware.go](backend/web/routes/middleware.go)\n\n**Two middleware functions:**\n\n### RequireJWTGlobal [middleware.go:22-55](backend/web/routes/middleware.go#L22-L55)\n- Enforces JWT auth on all routes EXCEPT those matching `DefaultPublicPaths` (includes `/auth/`, `/docs`, `/openapi.json`, `/r/`)\n- Extracts token from `SessionCookieName` cookie\n- **Calls`ParseJWT`** to validate\n- Checks `blacklist.IsBlacklisted(claims.ID)` for logged-out tokens\n- Stores claims in Gin context and stdlib context\n\n### RequireJWT [middleware.go:87-112](backend/web/routes/middleware.go#L87-L112)\n- Used on protected Huma routes (registered with `protectedGroup`)\n- Same logic: extract cookie → ParseJWT → blacklist check → store in contexts\n- Returns 401 Unauthorized for any step failure\n\n**Claims Context Storage:** [middleware.go:52-54](backend/web/routes/middleware.go#L52-L54)\n```go\nc.Set(string(CtxKeyJWTClaims), claims)\nc.Request = c.Request.WithContext(\n    context.WithValue(c.Request.Context(), ctxKeyJWTClaimsStd{}, claims),\n)\n```\n\n**Retrieval Helper:** [middleware.go:68](backend/web/routes/middleware.go#L68)\n```go\nfunc GetJWTClaimsFromContext(ctx context.Context) *JWTClaims {\n    claims, _ := ctx.Value(ctxKeyJWTClaimsStd{}).(*JWTClaims)\n    return claims\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Existing typ/type Claim Handling\n\n**alg (Algorithm) Header Check Only** [jwt.go:79, 123](backend/web/routes/jwt.go#L79):\n```go\nif _, ok := t.Method.(*jwt.SigningMethodHMAC); !ok {\n    return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unexpected signing method: %v\", t.Header[\"alg\"])\n}\n```\n\n**No \"typ\" claim validation currently exists:**\n- Neither `CreateJWT` nor `CreatePreRegToken` set an explicit `typ` header\n- Neither `ParseJWT` nor `ParsePreRegToken` validate a `typ` header\n- The golang-jwt library will auto-include `\"typ\":\"JWT\"` in the header by default, but there's no explicit code handling it\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Points\n\n| Aspect | Details |\n|--------|---------|\n| **Full Session JWT Claims** | `user_id`, `user_name`, `email`, `sub` (user_id), `jti` (unique token ID), `iat`, `exp` (24h) |\n| **Pre-Reg Token Claims** | `provider`, `provider_user_id`, `email`, `display_name`, `iat`, `exp` (10m) |\n| **Token Location** | HttpOnly session cookie named `SessionCookieName` |\n| **Validation Points** | Signature (HMAC-SHA256), expiry, blacklist lookup |\n| **Blacklist Mechanism** | JWT ID (`jti`) checked against in-memory map; cleaned up hourly or on token expiry |\n| **Missing typ Handling** | No explicit `typ` claim validation; only `alg` header is checked |","tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01HRy5q6Q7tXpTC4aiduo2TW__vscode-1773898184754","cwd":"/home/alexl70/src/pet/linkshortener"}

